An Osun State Magistrates’ court presided by Olugbenga Oladoke on Tuesday sentenced 22 years Old Muraina Sodiq to six months imprisonment at Ile Ife Correctional Centre for stealing. The convict who is deaf and dumb was said to have broken into the shop of one Rafiu Haruna with intent to commit felony therein on March 15, 2020 at Oke baale area of Osogbo East bypass. The charge sheet disclosed that the convict stole one welding Engine valued N45,000 and one motor battery valued N18,000 which total valued N63,000. The convict whose charge sheet was interpreted to through sign language and his father’s assistance entered guilty plea to the two counts charges of house breaking and stealing levelled against him by the police. The offence committed is contrary to and punishable under sections 413 and 390 (9) of the Criminal Code Cap 34 Vol. II Laws of Osun State Nigeria 2002. The defence counsel, Okobe Nagite prayed  the court to be lenient with his client considering his disability adding that he was beaten to stupor when he was caught at the scene of the crime before they realised he was  deaf and dumb However, the police prosecutor,  Inspector Olayiwola Razaq opposed the bail application on the ground that the convict had earlier been convicted on similar case by Magistrates’ court ll Osogbo adding that his father can also testify to it. In his judgement, Magistrate, Olugbenga Oladoke sentenced Sodiq to six months imprisonment at Ile ife Correctional Centre. 